Turn your Raspberry Pi into a home surveillance camera
Pre-requisites:
	- Pi with Raspbian installed
	- USB Camera
	

Files:
	motion.conf - motion configuration file
	notify.cfg	- configuration file for notify.py
	notify.py	- python script that connects to Google account in order to upload to Google Docs and send notification emails
	setup.sh	- script to automate the setup of motion and configuration to utilize Google account
				
	
1. Download files
2. extract files
3. run following command
	sudo ./setup.sh

4. follow instructions to setup


Note:
Streaming will be available http://<ip_address>:7780 
	- I recommend viewing stream in VLC
	
	




